/-- Suppose `f` is locally integrable on `(0, ‚àû)`, is `O(x ^ (-a))` as `x ‚Üí ‚àû`, and is
`O(x ^ (-b))` as `x ‚Üí 0`. Then its Mellin transform is differentiable on the domain `b < re s < a`,
